response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: String Calculator\", \"description\": \"Create a function that takes two strings as input and returns the sum of their lengths.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef string_calculator(s1: str, s2: str) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `s1` (str): The first string.\\n- `s2` (str): The second string.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of the lengths of the two input strings.\\n\", \"code\": \"def string_calculator(s1: str, s2: str) -> int:\\n    return len(s1) + len(s2)\", \"tests\": [\"assert string_calculator('hello', 'world') == 10\", \"assert string_calculator('', 'hi') == 2\", \"assert string_calculator('abcde', '') == 5\"] }"
